Seventh Avenue, west side, north from a point between West 51st and 52nd Street's, showing prominently pavement conditions. Note the Sixth Avenue "El" on 53rd Street.

June 15, 1915

Borough President of Manhattan
No. 702

Seventh Avenue, west side, north from a point between West 51st and 52nd Street's, showing prominently pavement conditions. At 53rd Street appears the Sixth Avenue "El".

June 15, 1915

Borough President of Manhattan
No. 701

Seventh Avenue, north from W. 51st Street. On the right, at the N. E. corner of W. 52nd Street, is the warehouse of the Manhattan Storage and Warehouse Co. Also shown is the Sixth Avenue "I" running, at this point, on W. 53rd Street.

June 15, 1915

Borough President of Manhattan
NO. 700

Seventh Avenue, north from W. 51st Street, showing sidewalk conditions pursuant to the construction of the subway. In the background appears the Sixth Avenue "I" running at this point, on W. 53rd Street.

June 15, 1915

Borough President of Manhattan
No. 687

Seventh Avenue, north from W. 51st Street, showing sidewalk conditions pursuant to the construction of the subway. Also shown is the elevated structure of the Sixth Avenue "L," on W. 53rd Street.

June 15, 1915

Borough President of Manhattan
No. 691

Seventh Avenue, north from W. 51st Street, showing sidewalk, relative to the construction of the subway. At the N. E. corner is the Manhattan Storage Company's warehouse, and beyond it is the Sixth Avenue "L," running, at this point, on W. 53rd Street.

June 15, 1915

Borough President of Manhattan
NO. 693

seventh Avenue, north from W. 51st Street. In the background appears the Sixth Avenue "L" running, at this point, on W. 53rd Street.

Borough President of Manhattan
No. 697

Seventh Avenue, east side, north from W. 51st Street. Part of the Sixth Avenue "L" is visible on W. 53rd Street.

Borough President of Manhattan
NO. 690

Seventh Avenue, north from W. 51st. Street. Part of the Sixth Avenue "L" appears on W. 53rd Street.

June 15, 1915

Borough President of Manhattan
No. 692.

West 51st Street, south side, east from Seventh to Sixth Avenue's, showing the northerly side of the New York Railway's carbarn. This has been replaced by the present Hotel Taft.

Borough President of Manhattan
No. 883

Garages: South East corner of 51st and 7th Avenue.

W. 51st Street, north side, west from Seventh Avenue.

June 15, 1915

Borough President of Manhattan
No. 699

Seventh Avenue, at the S.E. corner of West 51st Street, showing details of the New York Railway's carbarn. This has been replaced by the present Hotel Taft.

October 31, 1915

Borough President of Manhattan
No. 914

Seventh Avenue, west side, from 51st to 52nd Streets, seen across the excavation on the N.E. corner of 51st Street.

October 22, 1927.

P.L. Sperr.

Seventh Ave., east side, north from West 51st to 52nd Streets. Shown at the N.E. corner of 51st Street, is the Hotel Victoria. On the extreme left, appears a portion of the Manhattan Storage and Warehouse Co's. Building, at the N.E. corner of 52nd Street.
About 1928.

Gift of E. M. Jenks.
Underwood.

Seventh Avenue, at the S.E. corner of West 51st Street, showing details of the New York Railway's carbarn. This has been replaced by the present Hotel Taft.

February 26, 1916

Borough President of Manhattan
No. 1066

(1) West 51st Street, south side, east from Seventh Ave. Parking lot shown, is at the rear of Roxy's Theatre (extreme right) and is between Seventh and Sixth Aves. Prominent buildings shown, is the R.K.O. Building, a unit of Radio City. Also note the General Electric Building (Lexington Ave), another building on this street.
Sept March 18, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) A view of the immediate foreground (parking lot) of No. 1, and showing the rears of buildings on the west side of Sixth Ave., between 51st and 50th Streets. Also shown is the uncompleted 70-story R.C.A. Building, with its 16-story Sixth Ave. Entrance.

September 11, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

(3) The same, at a later date.
September 11, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.
